"{\"uid\": \"news18.com-movies-tom-cruise-had-this-one-condition-before-performing-at-paris-olympics-2024-9052966.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Performing at the closing ceremony of the Paris Olympics 2024 wasn't just a no-pay thing for Tom Cruise but also had one other factor involved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mission Impossible actor laid down a major condition before agreeing to deliver the high-octane stunt in Paris, where he made a dramatic entrance by parachuting from the top of the stadium and riding a motorcycle with the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999956332886, \"rank\": 4.366608523885383e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Casey Wasserman, president and chairperson of the LA28 committee for the upcoming 2028 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, recently opened up about the Hollywood actor's involvement in the ceremony.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 384, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\"}, {\"begin\": 490, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999942464799393, \"rank\": 5.753606400692492e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 532, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999828985439, \"rank\": 1.71014029112515e-08, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He revealed that it was producer Ben Winston who had the idea to include Cruise for a brief moment, but the actor wanted to do the stunts himself.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 612, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Winston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The moment when Tom Cruise flew through the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 743, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 771, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What was your favourite part of the Paris 2024#ClosingCeremony?\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 824, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8662795736150694e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rewatch the best moments of the Games here \\u27a1\\ufe0fhttps://t.co/nyCSlAtUVZ#Paris2024#Olympics#LA28pic.twitter.com/wOO0Vx4M95  - The Olympic Games (@Olympics)August 13, 2024    Speaking at the CNBC x Boardroom: Game Plan event in Santa Monica, he said that while the original concept involved a stunt double, Cruise himself changed the plans.\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999964179551, \"rank\": 1.5178862212948027e-09, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"score\": 0.998841242059454, \"rank\": 0.0011600833848998604, \"text\": \"Santa Monica\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The best part of the story is we pitched on Zoom, and the original idea was a person in the stadium as a stunt double.\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoom_Video_Communications\", \"score\": 0.9966330845178187, \"rank\": 0.003236635238005197, \"text\": \"Zoom\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoom_Video_Communications\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoom_Video_Communications\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are like, 'Well, there is no way we are getting this.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are going to get four hours of filming time.\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will do the thing with the Hollywood sign; he will hand the thing off, and he's done.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe we will get the other stuff and the rest will be just a stunt double,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite Winston's concerns about Cruise's commitment to the event amid his busy schedule, he eventually made it to the main day.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He not only took part in the closing ceremony without payment but was also able to fit the physically demanding Olympic segment into his tight schedule and did his own stunts.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He finished filming Mission: Impossible at 6 PM in London and got right on a plane.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1948, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9996076111285825, \"rank\": 0.00039236462031679665, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He landed in Los Angeles at 4 AM and filmed the scene where he pulled onto a military plane.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999942464799393, \"rank\": 5.753606400692492e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In L.A., he does two jumps out of the plane.\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9998001822792427, \"rank\": 0.00019985765149101, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not like the first one, so he did a second jump.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then he helicoptered from Palmdale to the Hollywood sign, filmed from 1 until 5, helicoptered to Burbank Airport, and flew back to London,\\\" Wasserman recalled.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmdale_Transportation_Center\", \"score\": 0.8987411519654348, \"rank\": 0.11266742132723759, \"text\": \"Palmdale\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmdale_Transportation_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmdale_Transportation_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}, {\"begin\": 2306, \"end\": 2312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9996076111285825, \"rank\": 0.00039236462031679665, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"score\": 0.9999340792315662, \"rank\": 6.59211763553837e-05, \"text\": \"Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is worth mentioning that Tom Cruise is currently busy with the production of his yet-to-be-titled eighth Mission: Impossible movie.\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Latest Blogs\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2484, \"entities\": []}]}"